[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 381     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Step 5: Daily block release optimization.** Between quarterly re-optimizations, blocks go unfilled. A service that can't fill their Tuesday afternoon block 72 hours before the date should release it. But to whom? This lightweight daily optimization checks for releasable blocks and assigns them to the service with the highest waitlist pressure and compatible room requirements. It's a much simpler model (fewer variables, fewer constraints) and solves in milliseconds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 5: Handle block release decisions.** This is the real-time component. When a block release deadline passes (typically 72 hours before the block) and the assigned service hasn't filled the time, the block becomes available. This step scores candidate services for the released block and assigns it to the best match. It's a much simpler optimization than the quarterly schedule generation: one block, multiple candidates, score and assign. Speed matters here because released blocks need to be visible to other services immediately.
[0m[49m[39m  382, 389[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  383, 390[0m:[39m[49m ```pseudocode
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 384     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m FUNCTION daily_release_check(date, release_threshold_hours=72):
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 385     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Find blocks within the release window that haven't been filled.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 386     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     upcoming_blocks = query DynamoDB for blocks on date
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 387     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     releasable = filter upcoming_blocks where:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 388     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         hours_until_block < release_threshold_hours
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 389     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         AND cases_scheduled == 0
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 390     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         AND not already_released
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION handle_block_release(room, block, releasing_service):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Fetch current demand signals: which services have cases waiting for OR time?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     waitlist = query scheduling system for pending cases without assigned OR time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Score each candidate service for this released block
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates = empty list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each service s with pending cases on the waitlist:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF service s can use this room (equipment check):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             score = compute_release_score(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 cases_waiting: count of pending cases for service s,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 average_case_revenue: contribution margin for service s cases,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 time_since_last_block: days since service s last had a released block,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 utilization_history: service s historical utilization rate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             append {service: s, score: score} to candidates
[0m[49m[39m  391, 406[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 392     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     IF releasable is empty:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 393     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         RETURN "No blocks to release today"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Sort by score, assign to highest
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sort candidates by score descending
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     winner = candidates[0]
[0m[49m[39m  394, 410[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 395     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // For each releasable block, find the best recipient.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 396     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     FOR each block in releasable:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 397     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         // Who wants this block? Check waitlist demand by service.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 398     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         eligible_services = services where:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 399     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             room capabilities match service requirements
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 400     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             AND service has active waitlist (patients needing surgery)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 401     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             AND service is not over their maximum allocation this week
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 402     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 403     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         IF eligible_services is empty:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 404     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             MARK block as "open pool" (first-come, first-served)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 405     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         ELSE:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 406     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             // Assign to service with highest waitlist pressure.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 407     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             // Pressure = patients_waiting / current_allocated_blocks
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 408     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             best_service = eligible_services sorted by waitlist_pressure descending, take first
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 409     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             ASSIGN block to best_service
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 410     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             NOTIFY scheduling team via SNS: "Block released to {best_service}"
